---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Work"
  description="Draft work index for Can Ocek across software, data, business systems, music, and research."
>
  <header class="page-header container narrow">
    <p class="eyebrow">Work</p>
    <h1>Selected work</h1>
    <p class="lede">
      A first route for projects across technical systems, business platforms, music, and earlier
      research. Full project entries will be added once the content collection is implemented.
    </p>
  </header>

  <section class="section" aria-labelledby="work-drafts-title">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="two-column">
        <div>
          <p class="eyebrow">Draft set</p>
          <h2 id="work-drafts-title">Initial project areas</h2>
        </div>
        <ul class="meta-list">
          <li>
            <strong>Web intelligence and semantic retrieval pipeline</strong>
            <p>
              Technical case study area for data collection, structured storage, and retrieval.
              Exact title, metrics, and team responsibilities need source confirmation.
            </p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Music performance, arrangement, and production</strong>
            <p>
              A central creative body of work covering performance, recording, production, live
              audio, and video once media links are selected.
            </p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Salesforce record-label CRM design</strong>
            <p>
              A technical-business CRM design or training case. It should not be described as a
              deployed client system unless that is later verified.
            </p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Procedural planet generation</strong>
            <p>
              Earlier Unity and C# work around procedural generation, chunking, mesh construction,
              and movement systems.
            </p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Dijkstra versus A* pathfinding research</strong>
            <p>
              A compact technical retrospective for the IB Extended Essay once the original paper
              is used as the source for results.
            </p>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
